l like Charlie
and l've got my fingers crossed.

953
01:18:38,820 --> 01:18:40,988
Why did you go into hiding?

954
01:18:41,030 --> 01:18:43,866
- l knew they would pick me up.
- What had you done?

955
01:18:43,907 --> 01:18:48,995
You Americans always assume you must
do something before you can be arrested.

956
01:18:49,037 --> 01:18:52,915
- Isn't that the way it usually works?
- Not here, Mr Horman.

957
01:18:52,956 --> 01:18:56,293
lt's crazy, Charlie being arrested by them,

958
01:18:56,335 --> 01:18:59,129
when some people thought
he was from the CIA.

959
01:18:59,170 --> 01:19:00,422
What?

960
01:19:00,463 --> 01:19:04,300
Charlie was always asking questions,
taking notes on everrything.

961
01:19:05,258 --> 01:19:08,220
- l warned him.
- And?

962
01:19:08,261 --> 01:19:10,973
He just laughed and took a note.

963
01:19:14,059 --> 01:19:17,603
He will come back, Beth, just as Carlos has.

964
01:19:25,402 --> 01:19:28,613
- This is all of them, Colonel?
- Me temo que sí.

965
01:19:29,781 --> 01:19:33,033
One form for each prisoner
who was held and released.

966
01:19:33,075 --> 01:19:36,828
- But none for my son?
- That means that he was not here.

967
01:19:37,787 --> 01:19:39,873
Come and check for yourself.

968
01:19:39,913 --> 01:19:42,375
l thought Frank Teruggi was released.

969
01:19:42,417 --> 01:19:43,960
Who?

970
01:19:44,000 --> 01:19:47,504
Teruggi. The man arrested
with David Holloway.

971
01:19:47,546 --> 01:19:50,340
Very sorry. l don't recall his name.

972
01:19:51,340 --> 01:19:53,426
Shall we?

973
01:20:07,646 --> 01:20:11,108
'Atención, su atención...'

974
01:20:20,742 --> 01:20:22,827
Go ahead, Mr Horman.

975
01:20:37,088 --> 01:20:40,926
l-l can't seem to.
You go ahead. You...you start.

976
01:20:42,552 --> 01:20:45,513
Charlie, this is Beth.

977
01:20:48,306 --> 01:20:50,726
l'm here with your dad, Charlie,

978
01:20:52,060 --> 01:20:54,146
and the American consul.

979
01:20:56,980 --> 01:20:59,067
So, ifyou can hear me,

980
01:21:01,943 --> 01:21:04,696
please come out so we can take you home.

981
01:21:18,083 --> 01:21:20,168
Charles Horman,

982
01:21:21,378 --> 01:21:24,130
this is your father, Edmund.

983
01:21:27,466 --> 01:21:30,677
l'm here in the hope
that you can hear me.

984
01:21:42,396 --> 01:21:44,690
Charles. Charles.

985
01:21:46,608 --> 01:21:48,693
Do you remember when we...

986
01:21:48,734 --> 01:21:53,948
took that trip together across county
from LA to New York?

987
01:21:58,200 --> 01:22:00,286
Just the two of us?

988
01:22:11,463 --> 01:22:14,382
That's him. Oh, my God, that's him!

989
01:22:14,424 --> 01:22:18,010
- No, it's not. It's not him, Ed.
- Charles!

990
01:22:18,552 --> 01:22:20,763
lt's not him. It's not him, Ed.

991
01:22:24,348 --> 01:22:26,434
My father cannot come here,

992
01:22:27,434 --> 01:22:32,147
but how about some ice cream
with my dinner, Colonel Espinoza?

993
01:22:34,483 --> 01:22:37,944
Ambassador,
my friends have talked to refugees

994
01:22:37,985 --> 01:22:41,155
in the Swedish, Mexican
and French embassies.

995
01:22:41,196 --> 01:22:44,116
The man they must see is here
in your embassy.

996
01:22:44,157 --> 01:22:47,411
All these people
are here for protection.

997
01:22:47,451 --> 01:22:51,706
- l am responsible for their lives.
- Oh, come on, look at them.

998
01:22:51,747 --> 01:22:53,833
Do they look like assassins?

999
01:22:55,500 --> 01:22:57,586
Ve y dile que no son problema.

1000
01:22:57,627 --> 01:23:01,465
- Beth. Mr Horman.
- OK, Kate. This way.

1001
01:23:12,975 --> 01:23:16,519
You must remember,
Mr Paris is a desperate man.

1002
01:23:24,901 --> 01:23:28,863
- How many refugees have you got here?
- About 800, 900.

1003
01:23:43,042 --> 01:23:46,671
'There were four of them
in Lutz's office.'

1004
01:23:46,711 --> 01:23:51,049
The general, of course, the colonel,
my friend, who told me of this,

1005
01:23:51,090 --> 01:23:53,677
- and the American.
- The prisoner?

1006
01:23:53,718 --> 01:23:57,472
The American officer.
No, the prisoner was in the next room.

1007
01:23:57,513 --> 01:24:00,057
- Was he alive?
- More or less.

1008
01:24:00,098 --> 01:24:02,184
What do you mean, ''more or less''?

1009
01:24:02,225 --> 01:24:07,105
- l'm only telling you what l heard.
- What does ''more or less'' mean?

1010
01:24:07,147 --> 01:24:11,651
Well, apparently he had been roughed up
during interrogation.

1011
01:24:11,691 --> 01:24:14,820
- How badly?
- l don't know. l wasn't there.

1012
01:24:14,861 --> 01:24:19,032
- Your friend was?
- My former friend, Mr Horman.

1013
01:24:19,073 --> 01:24:21,993
Nobody in this regime
is my friend any longer.

1014
01:24:22,034 --> 01:24:24,954
Who was the American officer in the room?

1015
01:24:24,996 --> 01:24:28,415
Who knows? The ministy is full of them.

1016
01:24:29,082 --> 01:24:33,920
Their Milgroup office is down the hall
from the general. This is a scoop for you.

1017
01:24:33,962 --> 01:24:36,130
Oh, Paris, everryone knows that.

1018
01:24:36,172 --> 01:24:40,926
Did they mention the prisoner?
Did they call the prisoner by name?

1019
01:24:40,967 --> 01:24:43,470
- Horseman?
- Horman?

1020
01:24:43,512 --> 01:24:45,847
Maybe. Horman, sure.

1021
01:24:45,889 --> 01:24:49,725
Horman. If l had been there,
l would know for sure.

1022
01:24:50,976 --> 01:24:55,355
l am an honour graduate
of your police academy in Washington.

1023
01:24:55,396 --> 01:25:00,360
l like America. There it is more democratic
and someday l hope to...

1024
01:25:00,401 --> 01:25:06,073
Paris, please. Just tell them what
the General Lutz said about the prisoner.

1025
01:25:06,114 --> 01:25:08,325
- Who is Lutz?
- He's the...

1026
01:25:08,367 --> 01:25:11,953
He's the head of the local version of the CIA.

1027
01:25:11,995 --> 01:25:14,539
He said the man must disappear.

1028
01:25:14,579 --> 01:25:18,459
- Oh, my God! Why?
- He knew too much.

1029
01:25:18,499 --> 01:25:20,794
- About what?
- l don't know.

1030
01:25:21,711 --> 01:25:25,757
But only a few verry important people
have been detained,

1031
01:25:25,797 --> 01:25:28,676
most of them were killed after interrogation.

1032
01:25:28,717 --> 01:25:32,846
- The others were sent to camps.
- What happened to my son?

1033
01:25:33,597 --> 01:25:36,099
They drove him back to the stadium.

1034
01:25:37,516 --> 01:25:40,478
How can you order the disappearance
of an American?

1035
01:25:40,519 --> 01:25:44,315
- l didn't order his disappearance!
- Ed, he didn't.

1036
01:25:44,355 --> 01:25:47,025
l'm a police officer but l'm not a murderer.

1037
01:25:47,067 --> 01:25:52,071
- We know you're a good man...
- l have worked for many governments.

1038
01:25:52,112 --> 01:25:56,408
Some, their politics l agreed with.
Others, not so much.

1039
01:25:56,450 --> 01:26:00,078
l have worked now
for the junta for two weeks,

1040
01:26:00,119 --> 01:26:02,205
but these are Nazis.

1041
01:26:03,790 --> 01:26:08,752
They are destroying everrything
that was beautiful about this county.

1042
01:26:08,793 --> 01:26:13,090
What we need to know is
can they order an American to disappear

1043
01:26:13,131 --> 01:26:16,259
without consulting the Americans first?

1044
01:26:17,427 --> 01:26:19,512
No, they wouldn't dare.

1045
01:26:20,887 --> 01:26:22,973
How can l verify that?

1046
01:26:24,808 --> 01:26:26,685
You can't.

1047
01:26:29,145 --> 01:26:31,230
What's gonna happen to these people?

1048
01:26:31,271 --> 01:26:35,025
Safe for the moment.
Later, they'll be deported.

1049
01:26:35,067 --> 01:26:39,654
- What about Paris?
- He's not even close to getting out of here.

1050
01:26:39,695 --> 01:26:43,950
- Why does he talk?
- If he gets enough press, they won't kill him.

1051
01:26:43,990 --> 01:26:47,369
They won't dare to.
It's like the old switch-hitting game.

1052
01:26:47,411 --> 01:26:49,496
Only way to survive.

1053
01:26:53,374 --> 01:26:57,378
Do you think that prisoner
in the other room was Charles?

1054
01:26:57,419 --> 01:26:59,505
What do you think?

1055
01:27:01,215 --> 01:27:03,675
What could Charles know
that's so important?

1056
01:27:03,716 --> 01:27:08,304
- Probably what he discovered in Viña.
- Do you still have his notes?

1057
01:27:08,346 --> 01:27:10,765
- Yeah, at the hotel.

1058
01:27:29,322 --> 01:27:32,742
- Stop it! Stop it!
- Ed, you'll get shot!

1059
01:27:32,783 --> 01:27:35,870
- Mr Horman.
- Stop! Stop it!

1060
01:27:35,910 --> 01:27:37,872
Good God!

1061
01:27:37,913 --> 01:27:39,998
Shut this.

1062
01:27:41,123 --> 01:27:43,543
Were you tying to get us all killed?

1063
01:27:43,584 --> 01:27:45,044
l'm sorry.

1064
01:27:45,086 --> 01:27:49,548
l am just beginning to get amully
sick and tired of all of this...

1065
01:27:49,589 --> 01:27:51,675
shit!

1066
01:27:51,716 --> 01:27:56,137
l saw your son do almost
the same damn dumb thing.

1067
01:27:56,178 --> 01:27:58,264
He did that?

1068
01:27:59,890 --> 01:28:03,310
''During the barbecue,
Ray Tower arrived.

1069
01:28:03,351 --> 01:28:05,771
''Later he drove us back to Santiago.

1070
01:28:05,813 --> 01:28:10,400
''Trip uneventful, aside roadblock incident,
detailed page 12.''

1071
01:28:10,441 --> 01:28:15,321
- Ray Tower drove 'em back?
- ''Later he drove us back to Santiago.''

1072
01:28:15,362 --> 01:28:17,948
Well, what? Does that mean something?

1073
01:28:22,327 --> 01:28:25,079
Go back to where they first meet Babcock.

1074
01:28:25,120 --> 01:28:28,165
''Charlie - 'May l borrow
that paper if you're through?'

1075
01:28:28,206 --> 01:28:32,669
''Babcock with a French Accent -
'You'd do better to ask in English.'''

1076
01:28:32,711 --> 01:28:34,796
You're French?

1077
01:28:34,838 --> 01:28:37,215
'Skip ahead to why he was there.'

1078
01:28:37,257 --> 01:28:43,262
- What are you doing down here?
- The navy sent me to do a job. She's done.

1079
01:28:43,303 --> 01:28:46,139
Any idea how long we'll be stuck in Viña?

1080
01:28:46,180 --> 01:28:50,393
About a week. Everything's all right.
The coup went verry smoothly.

1081
01:28:50,435 --> 01:28:55,230
- You're completely safe.
- Was it planned verry far in advance?

1082
01:28:55,271 --> 01:28:59,025
Tery, does a bear shit in the woods?

1083
01:28:59,067 --> 01:29:04,072
- Will the US recognise the government?
- That's up to the politicians.

1084
01:29:04,113 --> 01:29:08,659
''Red-haired woman appeared edgy.
Babcock stopped talking.''

1085
01:29:08,699 --> 01:29:11,453
Did Babcock introduce them to Patrick?

1086
01:29:11,495 --> 01:29:15,540
No, Charlie introduced himself.
''The next day in the lobby...''

1087
01:29:15,582 --> 01:29:17,667
Excuse me, Colonel.

1088
01:29:17,708 --> 01:29:21,670
''Colonel - 'Hello. What are you doing
in this neck of the woods?'

1089
01:29:21,712 --> 01:29:24,881
'''l'm Charles Horman.
This is my friend, Tery Simon.'

1090
01:29:24,923 --> 01:29:29,177
''l explained that we'd come for one day
and got stuck by the coup.''

1091
01:29:29,218 --> 01:29:32,680
Oh. You'll be here a while.
The roads are closed.

1092
01:29:32,720 --> 01:29:35,349
What's happening in the capital?

1093
01:29:36,308 --> 01:29:40,895
The militay's doing search-and-destroy
missions, just like in Vietnam.

1094
01:29:40,937 --> 01:29:44,065
There are bodies everywhere.
It's a royal mess.

1095
01:29:44,106 --> 01:29:47,276
How long before you think
the roads are open?

1096
01:29:47,316 --> 01:29:52,238
l don't know - but give me
your room number, l'll keep you posted.

1097
01:29:52,280 --> 01:29:54,115
l'd appreciate it.

1098
01:29:54,157 --> 01:29:56,659
''l'm terribly anxious about Beth.''

1099
01:30:12,380 --> 01:30:17,469
''Next morning Babcock was in lobby
with carton of Kents and without lady.''

1100
01:30:17,509 --> 01:30:20,638
- How's it going?
- Can't complain. Yourself?

1101
01:30:21,721 --> 01:30:23,599
l complain.

1102
01:30:23,641 --> 01:30:25,309
Uh-oh.

1103
01:30:26,768 --> 01:30:28,895
Where are you going when you leave?

1104
01:30:28,937 --> 01:30:30,897
Probably Bolivia.

1105
01:30:30,939 --> 01:30:35,151
- Bolivia is beautiful. You'll love it.
- That's what l hear.

1106
01:30:35,192 --> 01:30:37,278
So are you.

1107
01:30:38,611 --> 01:30:42,115
Of course, they have
their problems too, but...

1108
01:30:42,157 --> 01:30:45,785
lf they've got problems,
you'll probably go there next.

1109
01:30:45,826 --> 01:30:47,912
l know l'll go there next.

1110
01:30:51,080 --> 01:30:53,375
Sherlock, tell me something.

1111
01:30:53,416 --> 01:30:56,169
What would a naval engineer
be doing in Bolivia,

1112
01:30:56,210 --> 01:30:59,672
one of two landlocked countries
in Latin America?

1113
01:31:01,506 --> 01:31:03,467
Sir, any news?

1114
01:31:03,508 --> 01:31:07,929
lf l were you, l wouldn't be so anxious
to be there. It is a battlefield.

1115
01:31:07,970 --> 01:31:10,265
But sir...

1116
01:31:10,306 --> 01:31:14,894
Look, l have to meet somebody,
l'll be back in a couple of minutes.

1117
01:31:14,934 --> 01:31:20,565
l can take you to a place where you can
radio your parents and tell them you're safe.

1118
01:31:20,607 --> 01:31:22,817
- Couple of minutes.
- l know l'm safe.

1119
01:31:22,859 --> 01:31:25,069
lt's my wife l'm worried about.

1120
01:31:26,153 --> 01:31:27,821
You mind if l ask you a question?

1121
01:31:27,863 --> 01:31:30,199
Certainly. Go ahead.

1122
01:31:30,240 --> 01:31:33,159
- How do you feel about the coup?
- Verry good.

1123
01:31:33,201 --> 01:31:38,414
l've been in a lot of...
frustrating situations before this.

1124
01:31:38,456 --> 01:31:41,208
l was in Key West
waiting for the Bay of Pigs.

1125
01:31:41,249 --> 01:31:44,336
l even took an advanced scuba course
for that invasion.

1126
01:31:44,376 --> 01:31:49,674
lf Kennedy had provided decent air cover,
proper militay support there,

1127
01:31:49,714 --> 01:31:52,051
we wouldn't be having these problems here.

1128
01:31:52,093 --> 01:31:54,887
'''We arrived
at the home of Paul Baker,

1129
01:31:54,927 --> 01:31:57,472
'''where Naval Mission radio was installed.'''

1130
01:31:57,514 --> 01:32:02,101
Yeah, we received a cable
through Panama on September 14th.

1131
01:32:02,142 --> 01:32:06,188
''After radioing Dad,
Patrick offered to arrange a ride to Santiago

1132
01:32:06,229 --> 01:32:08,065
''with Captain Ray Tower, USN,

1133
01:32:08,105 --> 01:32:11,234
''who's returning there
with Herbert Porterfield.''

1134
01:32:11,275 --> 01:32:13,528
And the next day they came back?

1135
01:32:13,569 --> 01:32:17,698
Yeah. ''Checked out of hotel,
and Patrick drove us to his house

1136
01:32:17,739 --> 01:32:20,617
''for 'going away' barbecue.''

1137
01:32:20,658 --> 01:32:24,829
You're welcome to stay. We have a room,
if the hotel's too expensive.

1138
01:32:24,870 --> 01:32:27,582
That's verry nice of you, but thanks anmay.

1139
01:32:27,623 --> 01:32:30,334
- We have a Ping-Pong table too.
- Ping-Pong?

1140
01:32:30,375 --> 01:32:32,461
- Yes.
- No, thanks.

1141
01:32:33,795 --> 01:32:36,464
So are you guys friendly
with the local militay?

1142
01:32:36,505 --> 01:32:41,552
Some. l took Admiral Huidobro
to the United States to buy arms last July.

1143
01:32:41,593 --> 01:32:46,765
Militay's all right but the truck drivers
are the real heroes of this thing.

1144
01:32:46,806 --> 01:32:49,559
They wanna talk to Babcock again.

1145
01:32:49,601 --> 01:32:54,063
'''They considered us automatic allies
in anything the US might do.'''

1146
01:32:54,104 --> 01:32:56,774
He had to be a hamburger
to miss with a rocket.

1147
01:32:56,815 --> 01:33:01,111
- Charlie, you determined to go back?
- Mm-hm.

1148
01:33:01,153 --> 01:33:03,822
You know about the rebels?

1149
01:33:03,863 --> 01:33:07,033
Ray Tower is number two on their hit list.

1150
01:33:08,075 --> 01:33:10,160
l wouldn't ride with him.

1151
01:33:10,202 --> 01:33:12,704
l wanna see my wife. Thanks, anmay.

1152
01:33:16,874 --> 01:33:19,418
- Hello, Ray.
- Hi, Pat.

1153
01:33:19,460 --> 01:33:23,464
Well, here's your chauffeur.
Ray Tower, Charlie Horman.

1154
01:33:23,504 --> 01:33:25,591
- Pleased to meet you.
- And you.

1155
01:33:25,631 --> 01:33:29,636
So the boss of Milgroup
and the senior political officer

1156
01:33:29,676 --> 01:33:33,556
both happened to be in Viña
when the coup started.

1157
01:33:34,848 --> 01:33:38,393
''We came to do a job and it's done.''
What did Babcock mean by that?

1158
01:33:38,435 --> 01:33:41,730
Most people think the coup
was prepared in Viña.

1159
01:33:42,814 --> 01:33:45,483
Now, if we weren't involved in the coup

1160
01:33:45,525 --> 01:33:49,445
whatever Charlie saw or heard down there
is meaningless.

1161
01:33:49,485 --> 01:33:52,405
But if we were, it still doesn't mean much

1162
01:33:52,446 --> 01:33:55,074
but it could be significant.

1163
01:33:55,116 --> 01:33:58,411
At least enough for somebody
to take a look at his jacket.

1164
01:33:58,452 --> 01:34:00,829
- His what?
- His record.

1165
01:34:00,870 --> 01:34:05,083
They keep a file on everry American national
living down here.

1166
01:34:05,124 --> 01:34:09,837
Somebody decided to review that file
and found that Charlie worked for FIN.

1167
01:34:09,879 --> 01:34:13,424
They might conclude
that he was well worth watching.

1168
01:34:13,464 --> 01:34:15,884
Do you think that's what happened?

1169
01:34:15,926 --> 01:34:18,053
lt seems possible.

1170
01:34:23,307 --> 01:34:25,810
Doesn't look so good, does it?

1171
01:34:30,313 --> 01:34:33,483
OK, this gentleman
is gonna take us through.

1172
01:34:36,526 --> 01:34:38,612
Por acá.

1173
01:34:39,947 --> 01:34:43,241
- Hace mucho frío ahí abajo.
- Sí.

1174
01:34:43,283 --> 01:34:47,870
He says it's quite cold down here.
You better put on your sweater.

1175
01:34:53,375 --> 01:34:55,627
l think you should wait upstairs.

1176
01:34:55,669 --> 01:34:58,088
Todos ellos han sido identificados.

1177
01:34:58,128 --> 01:35:00,381
These have all been identified.

1178
01:35:00,422 --> 01:35:02,508
Vengan por acá.

1179
01:35:09,139 --> 01:35:13,059
Vengan, vengan.
Esos también han sido identificados.

1180
01:35:14,101 --> 01:35:17,021
These have all been identified as well.

1181
01:35:25,527 --> 01:35:28,614
Estos también han sido identificados.

1182
01:35:29,697 --> 01:35:31,784
These too, all identified.

1183
01:35:35,203 --> 01:35:37,914
Estos no han sido identificados.

1184
01:35:39,664 --> 01:35:43,252
The identities of these
have yet to be determined.

1185
01:36:23,828 --> 01:36:25,705
Ed?

1186
01:36:34,880 --> 01:36:36,340
Who is he?

1187
01:36:38,132 --> 01:36:39,759
Frank Teruggi.

1188
01:36:41,094 --> 01:36:43,346
Jesus Christ almighty!

1189
01:36:43,386 --> 01:36:45,723
Come on. Let's get her outta here.

1190
01:36:45,763 --> 01:36:50,560
Get off me. l'm not leaving here
until l've looked for my husband.

1191
01:36:50,601 --> 01:36:53,771
- Ed, give me a hand.
- You heard what she said.

1192
01:37:05,115 --> 01:37:10,286
Señores, por favor, quiero respuestas.

1193
01:37:10,328 --> 01:37:15,749
Por qué el cuerpo...?

1194
01:37:15,790 --> 01:37:20,628
Why wasn't the body discovered until now?
What took so long?

1195
01:37:20,670 --> 01:37:24,215
Por qué tardaron tanto
en descubrir el cadáver?

1196
01:37:29,886 --> 01:37:31,971
What kind of world is this?

1197
01:37:33,680 --> 01:37:35,975
You sound just like Charlie.

1198
01:37:43,398 --> 01:37:45,275
OK.

1199
01:37:46,024 --> 01:37:49,737
lt appears that Mr Teruggi was picked up
for a curfew violation

1200
01:37:49,778 --> 01:37:53,490
and detained at the stadium
and then released.

1201
01:37:53,531 --> 01:37:57,869
Then the carabineros found him
Iater that night, dead on the street.

1202
01:37:57,911 --> 01:38:02,081
Why did the State Department
tell me that he'd left the county?

1203
01:38:02,123 --> 01:38:07,669
l... Most likely some screw-up
at local immigration.

1204
01:38:10,630 --> 01:38:15,259
Phil, l'm not gonna leave this county
until l find my son, alive or dead.

1205
01:38:15,926 --> 01:38:18,220
What? No, it's just that...

1206
01:38:19,303 --> 01:38:23,975
everry new turn seems to lead us right back
to the beginning, you know?

1207
01:38:24,017 --> 01:38:26,102
Like we're going in circles.

1208
01:38:27,019 --> 01:38:29,104
We're going in circles!

1209
01:38:29,146 --> 01:38:33,858
Elizabeth! Can you...? Oh, yeah. OK.
That's better, dear.

1210
01:38:33,899 --> 01:38:36,611
What? No! l'm fine.

1211
01:38:36,653 --> 01:38:38,946
l'm just pooped, that's all.

1212
01:38:40,029 --> 01:38:42,449
Beth? Yeah, she's all right.

1213
01:38:43,491 --> 01:38:45,243
What?

1214
01:38:45,284 --> 01:38:48,371
Yes. Yes, dear, l will. And you too.

1215
01:38:49,871 --> 01:38:52,041
God bless you, Liz.

1216
01:39:19,981 --> 01:39:21,859
Earthquake.

1217
01:39:28,363 --> 01:39:31,033
Ed, not the elevator!

1218
01:39:39,207 --> 01:39:42,501
Don't stay in the windows.
It's dangerous!

1219
01:39:42,543 --> 01:39:46,296
Señores, no se queden
en las ventanas, es peligroso.

1220
01:39:46,338 --> 01:39:50,133
- Don't stay in the window. It's dangerous.

1221
01:39:50,174 --> 01:39:54,846
Be calm. The hotel is earthquake-proof.
No need for alarm!

1222
01:39:56,388 --> 01:39:58,807
You can't go outside. It's curfew!

1223
01:39:59,975 --> 01:40:03,853
Hey, you! Don't go out!
Curfew! Please, don't.

1224
01:40:05,146 --> 01:40:07,523
- Go back to your...

1225
01:40:14,821 --> 01:40:19,951
Ladies and gentlemen,
please, go back to your rooms.

1226
01:40:19,992 --> 01:40:22,536
There is no more danger.

1227
01:40:22,577 --> 01:40:24,455
Vuelvan a las habitaciones,
no hay peligro ya.

1228
01:40:24,495 --> 01:40:27,749
- l'm sorry.
- It's all right. l don't mind.

1229
01:40:31,544 --> 01:40:33,629
You wanna go up?

1230
01:40:33,670 --> 01:40:35,756
l'm still tying to come down.

1231
01:40:35,797 --> 01:40:39,760
Beth, how about a drink, hm?

1232
01:40:39,801 --> 01:40:42,053
- Help you sleep.
- But not in the bar.

1233
01:40:50,310 --> 01:40:52,187
Thank you.

1234
01:40:53,313 --> 01:40:55,482
- A la vida.
- A la v...

1235
01:40:55,523 --> 01:40:58,526
To life. Charlie and l always say that.

1236
01:41:03,279 --> 01:41:05,157
Now...

1237
01:41:07,449 --> 01:41:10,119
- l owe you an apology.
- No, you don't.

1238
01:41:11,954 --> 01:41:15,332
For a long time now, l've sold you short,

1239
01:41:15,958 --> 01:41:17,834
both of you.

1240
01:41:17,875 --> 01:41:21,337
l don't really know why,
unless it's because l'm getting old.

1241
01:41:21,379 --> 01:41:23,464
And l'm verry stubborn.

1242
01:41:24,549 --> 01:41:26,634
Why don't you sit over here?

1243
01:41:34,348 --> 01:41:36,767
This past week, l've felt like...

1244
01:41:38,518 --> 01:41:41,313
my heart has just been torn out of me.

1245
01:41:42,314 --> 01:41:44,191
lt's OK.

1246
01:41:46,942 --> 01:41:49,028
l feel verry guilty.

1247
01:41:49,069 --> 01:41:51,155
Charlie always says guilt is like fear,

1248
01:41:51,196 --> 01:41:54,616
it's given to us for survival,
not destruction.

1249
01:41:59,871 --> 01:42:04,208
Beth, you're one of the most courageous
people l have ever met.

1250
01:42:04,917 --> 01:42:07,002
l mean it.

1251
01:42:10,879 --> 01:42:12,757
Thank you.

1252
01:42:17,969 --> 01:42:20,055
You think he's dead?

1253
01:42:24,100 --> 01:42:26,561
l don't know.

1254
01:42:26,601 --> 01:42:28,854
No. No, l don't...

1255
01:42:29,771 --> 01:42:31,857
think he's dead.

1256
01:42:32,690 --> 01:42:35,527
But that's not how you really feel, is it?

1257
01:42:37,945 --> 01:42:41,157
- l spoke to Elizabeth tonight.
- And?

1258
01:42:41,197 --> 01:42:45,285
She was speaking again with some people
from the Ford Foundation.

1259
01:42:45,326 --> 01:42:50,373
They think we should contact Peter Cooke.
He runs their office here.

1260
01:42:50,414 --> 01:42:52,875
Do you mind if l skip that one?

1261
01:42:52,917 --> 01:42:54,877
No.

1262
01:42:57,296 --> 01:43:00,549
You kids love each other
verry much, don't you?

1263
01:43:04,469 --> 01:43:09,098
l'm verry sorry, sir, but Mr Cooke
is out of the county until Monday.

1264
01:43:09,138 --> 01:43:12,351
- Oh...
- Can l be of some help?

1265
01:43:12,391 --> 01:43:15,937
Well, l was just paying a courtesy call
on Mr Cooke.

1266
01:43:15,979 --> 01:43:18,481
You're Mr Horman, aren't you?

1267
01:43:19,522 --> 01:43:24,278
Erm, why don't you come inside
and we can talk for a while?

1268
01:43:24,319 --> 01:43:27,447
- Well, l...
- Mr Horman, please come in.

1269
01:43:33,828 --> 01:43:38,165
Hi, l'm Peter Chernin.
l'm an economic advisor with the foundation.

1270
01:43:38,205 --> 01:43:40,750
Would you come with me for a moment?

1271
01:43:47,173 --> 01:43:49,258
Please, take a seat.

1272
01:44:03,436 --> 01:44:05,689
l have a friend l play golf with.

1273
01:44:06,480 --> 01:44:11,694
l won't identify him, but he works
for an English-speaking embassy here,

1274
01:44:11,734 --> 01:44:16,406
and he's close to someone who has
good contacts with the militay.

1275
01:44:17,449 --> 01:44:22,662
He thinks your son was executed
in the national stadium on September 19th.

1276
01:44:28,750 --> 01:44:31,169
That was nearly a month ago.

1277
01:44:31,211 --> 01:44:33,087
Yes, sir.

1278
01:44:38,217 --> 01:44:40,302
Could l...

1279
01:44:41,386 --> 01:44:44,097
speak to your friend or his contact?

1280
01:44:45,180 --> 01:44:48,476
No, l'm afraid not.
These are verry dangerous times.

1281
01:44:48,516 --> 01:44:50,769
l'll go anmhere, in any way.

1282
01:44:50,811 --> 01:44:54,231
You can tie my hands.
You can blindfold me. You can...

1283
01:44:54,272 --> 01:44:57,692
l'm sorry. l am sorry, but l can't do that.

1284
01:45:09,494 --> 01:45:12,330
l probably shouldn't even have told you.

1285
01:45:14,790 --> 01:45:18,043
This is a terrible, terrible tragedy.

1286
01:45:20,461 --> 01:45:22,547
Just give me a name.

1287
01:45:23,505 --> 01:45:25,299
Please.

1288
01:45:25,341 --> 01:45:27,218
Just...

1289
01:45:35,892 --> 01:45:38,144
That's all right. l understand.

1290
01:45:39,603 --> 01:45:41,689
Thank you for telling me.

1291
01:46:10,504 --> 01:46:14,592
Ed. Ed. The ambassador is waiting for you
in the ballroom.

1292
01:46:15,759 --> 01:46:19,346
We've been tying to reach you.
We may have some good news.

1293
01:46:19,388 --> 01:46:21,473
What would that be?

1294
01:46:21,515 --> 01:46:26,102
That my son was executed in the stadium
three days after his arrest?

1295
01:46:26,143 --> 01:46:28,730
Wait. Who told you that? Ed, wait.

1296
01:46:29,814 --> 01:46:32,066
Ah, good, Consul, you found him.

1297
01:46:32,108 --> 01:46:34,610
Mr Horman, this is Mr Samuel Cross.

1298
01:46:35,776 --> 01:46:39,322
Gentlemen, perhaps we'd be
more comfortable over here.

1299
01:46:39,364 --> 01:46:44,327
Mr Cross is a journalist with good access
to left-wing circles down here

1300
01:46:44,368 --> 01:46:48,705
and he's dug up some
interesting information about your son.

1301
01:46:50,039 --> 01:46:53,168
l believe that your son's alive and well,
Mr Horman.

1302
01:46:53,208 --> 01:46:57,421
Captain Tower asked me to make inquiries
about Charles's whereabouts.

1303
01:46:57,462 --> 01:47:01,258
l spoke with a guy who's helping
political refugees escape.

1304
01:47:01,300 --> 01:47:06,346
His organisation has secured credentials
for three Americans to leave Santiago.

1305
01:47:06,387 --> 01:47:08,472
One of them was your son.

1306
01:47:09,889 --> 01:47:12,267
- Where is he?
- He's in the north.

1307
01:47:12,308 --> 01:47:16,271
He should be out of the county
sometime next week.

1308
01:47:16,312 --> 01:47:18,356
Can l contact him?

1309
01:47:18,397 --> 01:47:22,193
l'm afraid you can't. But l'll lay odds
he's home in New York before...

1310
01:47:22,234 --> 01:47:24,737
Will you please get him out of here?

1311
01:47:24,777 --> 01:47:28,740
Now, l said ''please''.
l wanna speak to the two of you alone.

1312
01:47:28,781 --> 01:47:32,702
Mr Cross, thank you.
Mr Horman has new information

1313
01:47:32,744 --> 01:47:34,829
and l'll check it out right away.

1314
01:47:34,869 --> 01:47:37,373
Yes, you do that. You call General Lutz.

1315
01:47:40,332 --> 01:47:43,044
l believe my son was killed by the militay.

1316
01:47:43,086 --> 01:47:46,797
- Where'd you hear that?
- l do not think they would dare do that

1317
01:47:46,839 --> 01:47:49,800
unless an American official
co-signed a kill order.

1318
01:47:49,841 --> 01:47:54,971
That's a hell of a statement considering
we're here to protect American citizens.

1319
01:47:55,012 --> 01:47:59,684
This mission has done everrything
humanly possible to locate your son.

1320
01:47:59,725 --> 01:48:02,895
l think you knew
he was dead from the start.

1321
01:48:02,937 --> 01:48:05,272
lf we knew, why wouldn't we tell you?

1322
01:48:05,313 --> 01:48:09,150
- l don't know but l'll find out.
- Why would we want him dead?

1323
01:48:09,192 --> 01:48:11,903
Because he knew
of our involvement in the coup.

1324
01:48:11,944 --> 01:48:15,698
We're not involved.
Our position has been completely neutral.

1325
01:48:15,738 --> 01:48:17,991
That is a bald-faced lie!

1326
01:48:18,032 --> 01:48:21,995
How can you say a thing like that
when you have army colonels,

1327
01:48:22,035 --> 01:48:26,040
- naval engineers, all over Viña del Mar?
- Please, sit down.

1328
01:48:26,081 --> 01:48:29,376
lt's obvious you're harbouring
some misconception

1329
01:48:29,417 --> 01:48:33,129
- regarding our role here.
- What is your role here...

1330
01:48:33,171 --> 01:48:37,049
besides endorsing a regime
that murders thousands of human beings?

1331
01:48:37,091 --> 01:48:38,759
Let's level with each other.

1332
01:48:38,800 --> 01:48:42,888
lf you hadn't been involved
in this unfortunate incident

1333
01:48:42,929 --> 01:48:48,351
you'd be sitting at home complacent
and more or less oblivious to all of this.

1334
01:48:52,353 --> 01:48:56,108
This mission is pledged
to protect American interests.

1335
01:48:56,149 --> 01:48:58,360
Well, they're not mine.

1336
01:48:58,400 --> 01:49:02,113
There are over 3,OOO US firms
doing business down here,

1337
01:49:02,155 --> 01:49:04,949
and those are American interests.

1338
01:49:04,989 --> 01:49:07,242
ln other words, your interests.

1339
01:49:08,452 --> 01:49:11,830
l'm concerned with the preservation
of a way of life.

1340
01:49:11,870 --> 01:49:13,957
And a damn good one.

1341
01:49:15,458 --> 01:49:18,669
Maybe that's why there's nobody out there.

1342
01:49:22,338 --> 01:49:24,424
You can't have it both ways.

1343
01:49:33,432 --> 01:49:36,726
l don't know what happened to your kid, Ed,

1344
01:49:36,768 --> 01:49:41,564
but l understand he was a bit of a snoop.

1345
01:49:42,355 --> 01:49:47,027
He poked his nose in dangerous places
where he really didn't belong.

1346
01:49:47,069 --> 01:49:49,571
Now, suppose...

1347
01:49:50,280 --> 01:49:52,573
l went up to your town, New York,

1348
01:49:52,614 --> 01:49:56,243
and l started messing
around with the Mafia.

1349
01:49:56,285 --> 01:49:58,829
l wind up dead in the East River.

1350
01:49:58,870 --> 01:50:01,540
And my wife, or my father,

1351
01:50:01,581 --> 01:50:06,002
complains to the police
because they didn't protect me.

1352
01:50:07,085 --> 01:50:10,547
They really wouldn't have much of a case,
would they?

1353
01:50:11,589 --> 01:50:14,509
You play with fire, you get burned.

1354
01:50:42,658 --> 01:50:44,869
Just a minute. What's going on?

1355
01:50:44,910 --> 01:50:47,580
They wanna ask questions about Charlie.

1356
01:50:47,621 --> 01:50:50,040
- Who are you?
- l'm Inspector Rojas.

1357
01:50:50,081 --> 01:50:52,667
l am taking Mrs Horman to headquarters.

1358
01:50:52,709 --> 01:50:55,211
- For what?
- Interrogation.

1359
01:50:55,252 --> 01:50:57,338
She's not going anmhere.

1360
01:50:58,839 --> 01:51:00,925
- Ed?
- Wait a minute.

1361
01:51:03,801 --> 01:51:06,471
Get me the American consulate, please.

1362
01:51:06,512 --> 01:51:08,932
ls everrything all right?

1363
01:51:08,972 --> 01:51:12,726
- Ed, what's wrong?
- Nothing. Nothing, dear.

1364
01:51:12,767 --> 01:51:17,105
l'd like to speak to Consul Putnam.
This is Ed Horman calling.

1365
01:51:17,146 --> 01:51:20,066
What'd they say at the Ford Foundation?

1366
01:51:21,525 --> 01:51:25,279
- Consul, there's a... What's your name?
- Inspector Rojas.

1367
01:51:25,320 --> 01:51:28,448
An Inspector Rojas here, and he...

1368
01:51:28,489 --> 01:51:31,660
Oh, just a minute. He wants to speak to you.

1369
01:51:33,994 --> 01:51:36,080
Yes, Consul Putnam?

1370
01:51:36,997 --> 01:51:39,208
Oh, l understand.

1371
01:51:39,248 --> 01:51:40,876
Certainly.

1372
01:51:41,959 --> 01:51:43,962
l will do as you say.

1373
01:51:44,004 --> 01:51:46,089
Fine, sir. Thank you.

1374
01:51:48,800 --> 01:51:50,259
Yes?

1375
01:51:50,300 --> 01:51:52,177
Why?

1376
01:51:52,928 --> 01:51:56,348
Yes, all right. But if l have any trouble with...

1377
01:51:57,515 --> 01:52:00,268
l said, ''All right''. l'm going with you.

1378
01:52:02,227 --> 01:52:07,524
- Name of missing person?
- l've answered this a thousand times.

1379
01:52:07,566 --> 01:52:11,736
- Name of missing person, please.
- Charles Horman.

1380
01:52:12,486 --> 01:52:14,530
Date of disappearance?

1381
01:52:14,571 --> 01:52:16,657
September 16th.

1382
01:52:18,825 --> 01:52:21,828
- Time of disappearance?
- l'm not sure.

1383
01:52:21,869 --> 01:52:25,498
He was arrested that afternoon.
l don't know when.

1384
01:52:25,540 --> 01:52:29,627
- Time unknown.
- Hay una Ilamada para el señor Horman.

1385
01:52:29,668 --> 01:52:31,754
You have a call, sir.

1386
01:52:33,295 --> 01:52:35,382
l'll be right back.

1387
01:52:36,465 --> 01:52:39,510
Place of birth?
New York.

1388
01:52:40,468 --> 01:52:42,555
ln this room.

1389
01:52:49,893 --> 01:52:51,771
Hello?

1390
01:52:51,812 --> 01:52:56,150
l looked into that, Ed,
and it appears that you were right.

1391
01:52:57,776 --> 01:53:01,237
We've been informed that the body
has been identified

1392
01:53:01,278 --> 01:53:03,948
through a recheck of morgue fingerprints.

1393
01:53:05,908 --> 01:53:08,118
Positive identification?

1394
01:53:08,160 --> 01:53:10,370
'Yes, absolutely...

1395
01:53:10,412 --> 01:53:12,539
'positive. They found him.

1396
01:53:13,706 --> 01:53:17,001
'He was...buried in a wall.'

1397
01:53:18,084 --> 01:53:21,255
ln a wall? l don't understand.

1398
01:53:22,213 --> 01:53:25,425
They do that. It's quite common down here.

1399
01:53:32,931 --> 01:53:35,309
W-Was he killed in the stadium?

1400
01:53:36,476 --> 01:53:38,562
- 'lt looks that way.'
- l see.

1401
01:53:41,564 --> 01:53:43,441
Goodbye.

1402
01:54:12,633 --> 01:54:15,218
His political affiliation?

1403
01:54:20,265 --> 01:54:22,350
Please, Mrs Horman.

1404
01:54:26,145 --> 01:54:28,230
We're going home.

1405
01:54:30,649 --> 01:54:32,650
l love you, Ed.

1406
01:55:48,550 --> 01:55:50,802
l want you to contact the militay.

1407
01:55:50,843 --> 01:55:55,472
l want you to demand all Charles'
personal effects stolen from this house.

1408
01:55:55,513 --> 01:55:58,850
- That's not verry realistic.
- Every drawing, everry notebook,

1409
01:55:58,891 --> 01:56:01,144
everry article my son wrote or had.

1410
01:56:01,186 --> 01:56:03,813
- Ed, l can't go to the...
- Do it!

1411
01:56:03,854 --> 01:56:06,941
l don't care whether it's a cinch
or difficult as hell.

1412
01:56:06,981 --> 01:56:09,901
- l want it done.
- l'll ty.

1413
01:56:12,069 --> 01:56:14,155
Right here, please.

1414
01:56:15,948 --> 01:56:18,159
- Good. That takes care of it.
- That's it?

1415
01:56:18,200 --> 01:56:19,868
- Yes.
- OK.

1416
01:56:19,910 --> 01:56:21,995
When will he be sent home?

1417
01:56:22,037 --> 01:56:24,581
Erm, l'd say a few days.

1418
01:56:24,622 --> 01:56:28,835
We've got to get some other clearances.
Nothing important.

1419
01:56:28,875 --> 01:56:31,003
We should ship him home by Friday.

1420
01:56:31,044 --> 01:56:33,881
- You're sure?
- You've got my word on it.

1421
01:56:37,842 --> 01:56:41,179
Wait, there's just one more thing. Just one.

1422
01:56:41,219 --> 01:56:43,806
Did you mention the shipping charges?

1423
01:56:43,848 --> 01:56:47,684
